    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>LXVI.5</citedRange></bibl> and copy of [Negri], Sardinian consul in Tripoli,
                    whence <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5163</citedRange></bibl> and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4864</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#farag-jmr1978-1979"/>, p. 232, n. <citedRange>1.c.5</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>37.1679, 5</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>078500</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#applebaum1962"/>, pp. <citedRange>34-35</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62844"><name nymRef="#Ἀναξίλας"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξίλ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan></name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65827"><name nymRef="#Τιμόλας"><expan><abbr>Τιμόλ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#farag-jmr1978-1979"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξίλ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#franz1853 #applebaum1962"><unclear>Ἀ</unclear>ναξί<unclear>α</unclear></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <app loc="2"><lem resp="#farag-jmr1978-1979"><expan><abbr>Τιμόλ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#farag-jmr1978-1979"><expan><abbr>Τιμόλ</abbr><ex>α</ex></expan></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#applebaum1962">Τιμολ<supplied reason="lost">ίου</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Anaxilas. Timolas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Anaxilas. Timolas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Anaxilas. Timolas.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>At line 1, we follow Reynolds' reading. However, other possibilities exist: the masculine <foreign xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξίλ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan></foreign> might also be at 
                    the genitive: <foreign xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξίλ</abbr><ex>α</ex></expan></foreign>, while the corresponding feminine <foreign xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξίλ</abbr><ex>α</ex></expan></foreign> or even <foreign xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Ἀναξιλ</abbr><ex>έα</ex></expan></foreign> would also fit this uncomplete name. The same for the second name.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
